Machine Learning (ML) Overview Roadmap
Created by Triveni Paswan using various online resources, research papers, official documentation, and learning references.

1. Introduction to Machine Learning

Definition:
Machine Learning (ML) is a subset of Artificial Intelligence (AI) that enables computers to learn patterns from data and make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed.

Goal:
To build systems that can automatically learn from data and improve performance over time.

Examples:
- Netflix Recommendations
- YouTube Recommendations
- Spam Email Detection
- Credit Card Fraud Detection
- Stock Price Prediction

2. AI vs ML vs DL

Artificial Intelligence (AI)
Definition:
Creating intelligent systems capable of simulating human intelligence.

Machine Learning (ML)
Definition:
Subset of AI that learns from data.

Deep Learning (DL)
Definition:
Subset of ML using multi-layer neural networks.

Relationship:

AI
└── Machine Learning
    └── Deep Learning

